lioncub: First let us all sit in E seat. Open 1NT and show no 4-card major in response to stayman. So what does 2@H now show? It shows a weak hand with 5 hearts and 4 spades............and signs off in 2@H willing to play this in a possible 5-2 fit. Smolen is only used with game forcing hand.....forget it............never on this hand. So what went wrong? Let us have another look at W hand and decide.|
PG| ***** 6 ***** |


NT|
lioncub: THIS IS THE RULE............ONLY USE STAYMAN IF LOOKING FOR A 4/4 FIT IN ONE OF THE MAJORS. Of course still use it with 4/5......hoping to find fit in the 4-card suit. So how do you show 5-card suit?   NEVER use stayman.........use transfer sequence. |
PG| ***** 7 ***** |


NT|
Bidding should be:
              1NT-2@D
              2@H-2NT
That bidding shows an invitational hand with 5-card heart suit. Opener can pass........or sign off in 3@H with min hand and 3 hearts...........or bid 3NT with max and 2 hearts.........or bid 4@H with max and 3 hearts. This is a very instructive hand.........please be clear on my explanation. Questions?|
